# Dataset

This project uses the **Book-Crossing Dataset**, a widely used benchmark dataset for
recommender systems research, collected by Cai-Nicolas Ziegler from the Book-Crossing
community (bookcrossing.com).

CSV files are **not included in this repository** due to their size (~120 MB total).
Download them yourself and place them in this `data/` folder before running the scripts.

## Files required

| File | Description | Rows (raw) |
|---|---|---|
| `BX_Books.csv` | Book metadata: ISBN, title, author, year, publisher | ~271,000 |
| `BX-Users.csv` | User demographics: user ID, location, age | ~279,000 |
| `BX-Book-Ratings.csv` | User ratings: user ID, ISBN, rating (0–10) | ~1,150,000 |

## Where to get it

The dataset is publicly available from several mirrors, including:
- http://www2.informatik.uni-freiburg.de/~cziegler/BX/
- Kaggle: search "Book-Crossing Dataset"

## Format notes

- Delimiter: `;` (semicolon), fields quoted with `"`
- Encoding: `latin-1` (ISO-8859-1)
- Ratings of `0` are **implicit** (the user interacted with the book but left no
  explicit score) rather than a real preference score of zero. The pipeline filters
  these out before training the collaborative filtering model.

## After cleaning

`src/02_clean.py` outputs three cleaned CSVs into this same folder:
`books_clean.csv`, `users_clean.csv`, `ratings_clean.csv`. These are also excluded
from version control — regenerate them locally by running the pipeline.
